						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">much of [a commercial 16-bit game] was done in a wasteful way, because the resources allowed it.</div><br />And a lot of the fat could be cut, as seen in HKO games. I clarified this in the article.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">I'm totally skipping the PPU issues (graphics can always be dumbed down</div><br />That's fine. All that part talks about is the specific <em>kind</em> of dumbing down that will happen, as a way of preparing the reader for dropping one-fourth of the save at once.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">But another programmer that also likes this game might favor other aspects of it, or even find a very different technical approach to implementing the difficult things than you and succeed in creating his version of the game</div>
